Key learnings: (1) Tauri v2 ExitRequested NEVER fires on macOS Cmd-Q — the default Quit menu item calls std::process::exit(0) directly (Tauri issue #9198). Fix: enable_macos_default_menu(false) + custom menu with custom-quit item bound to CmdOrCtrl+Q. (2) tokio::signal::ctrl_c() catches SIGINT not SIGTERM, so sending SIGTERM to the sidecar kills it before graceful shutdown runs. Fix: don't use signals at all — run 'xpressclaw down' via the CLI binary to stop containers via the API, then kill the child process. (3) Window close → hide to tray uses on_window_event with CloseRequested + api.prevent_close() + window.hide().
